latestIgtvVideos.title: #MatchCornJeetega Contest 🎉
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Recently stumbled upon the new contest that @cornitos has launched for this IPL season called #MatchCornJeetega (do you see what they did there?). Essentially, you predict the winner of that day's IPL match, and also avail a flat 20% off on your favorite Cornitos nachos, snacks, and nuts. 

Here's how you can do it:

- Scan the QR code at the back of any Cornitos pack 
- It will take you to a site where you predict the winner, enter your details, and voila, you'd get a 20% off discount coupon
- Use the code to shop on shop.cornitos.in

Remember you get your 20% off discount coupon for participating as well even if your prediction is incorrect. So give it a shot! And you can also check the link in my bio to take part in the contest directly if you don't have any packet with you right now. #MatchCornJeetega #Cornitos

latestIgtvVideos.title: TOMATO FACIAL AT HOME 🍅
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Hey guys! It’s quarantine so I thought why not take care of your skin instead? Here’s a quick DIY TOMATO FACIAL for you all to try at home. 
For this , you’ll need:

STEP 1 : SANITISING 🧼 
It is important to sanitise your hands first . This will help prevent infections. You can wash your hands with soap and water or use a hand sanitiser.

STEP 2 : CLEANSING 🧊 
Tomato pulp + Raw Milk 
Mix these two together and apply it using a cotton pad on your face and neck.

STEP 3 : SCRUBBING 🍅 
Take half a tomato and rub sugar over  the cut part. Gently massage this tomato and sugar scrub over your face. Don’t be too harsh as the sugar granules can irritate the skin.

STEP 4 : MASKING 🧖‍♀️ Tomato pulp + sandalwood powder + Honey
Mix these well to form a face pack.

Apply it evenly on your face and let it dry for 15 minutes. Then, wash your face with normal tap water.

STEP 5 : MOISTURISING 🧴 
You can use your favourite moisturiser or Aloevera Gel to hydrate the skin and make it soft and supple. •
Tomato is a miracle food for skin. It acts as a natural sunscreen, treats open pores, helps in giving glowing skin, fades blemishes and prevents the first signs of ageing.

I’ll be posting more videos for skin care, let me know what do you think?
